cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.DS, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the analysis of time-varying network data and the dynamics of the underlying relations between entities. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a nonparametric model for dynamic networks that involves a Factorial Hidden Markov model. 
- cs.SD (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper may involve software implementation of the proposed model. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also less likely but possible as the paper deals with the extraction of a summary of the common structure and dynamics of the underlying relations between entities. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but possible as the paper involves modeling the birth and death of individual groups with respect to the dynamics of the network structure.
